rg/resource/Dublin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their entrance\", \"from\": 29, \"to\": 43}, {\"ngram\": \"the grand opening\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 64}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 68, \"to\": 86}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 116, \"to\": 120}, {\"ngram\": \"formal uniforms\", \"from\": 143, \"to\": 158}, {\"ngram\": \"the LW Pearl label\", \"from\": 242, \"to\": 260}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their white suits comprise two blazers (for the opening and closing ceremonies), a T-shirt, trousers and shoes.\", \"from\": 263, \"to\": 374, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their white suits\", \"from\": 263, \"to\": 280}, {\"ngram\": \"two blazers\", \"from\": 290, \"to\": 301}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening and closing ceremonies\", \"from\": 307, \"to\": 341}, {\"ngram\": \"a T-shirt\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 353}, {\"ngram\": \"trousers\", \"from\": 355, \"to\": 363}, {\"ngram\": \"shoes\", \"from\": 368, \"to\": 373}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sleeve is embroidered with the county emblem of each individual Olympian, each decorated with beads, sequins and stones.\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 443, \"end\": 451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999929938771723, \"rank\": 6.742835275210521e-06, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The sleeve\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 385}, {\"ngram\": \"the county emblem\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 423}, {\"ngram\": \"beads\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 478}, {\"ngram\": \"sequins\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"stones\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 498}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Four shamrocks in different techniques represent the four provinces of Ireland and embroidered on the inside face of the jacket is the name of the athlete, making it a personal keepsake.\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 571, \"end\": 578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999637894483017, \"rank\": 3.621181260317651e-05, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Four shamrocks\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 514}, {\"ngram\": \"different techniques\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 538}, {\"ngram\": \"the four provinces\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 567}, {\"ngram\": \"the inside face\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 613}, {\"ngram\": \"the jacket\", \"from\": 617, \"to\": 627}, {\"ngram\": \"the name\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 639}, {\"ngram\": \"the athlete\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the closing ceremony, a star strap around the neck of the jacket has been deliberately designed for comfort and to frame a medal for photography.\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 837, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 712}, {\"ngram\": \"a star strap\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 726}, {\"ngram\": \"the neck\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 742}, {\"ngram\": \"the jacket\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 756}, {\"ngram\": \"comfort\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 799}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 820}, {\"ngram\": \"photography\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 836}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other details include colour degradation on the T-shirt to symbolise the blue sky and green grass of Ireland, while a Tricolour in the side piping of the trousers is a subtle representation of the national flag.\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 1050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 940, \"end\": 947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999637894483017, \"rank\": 3.621181260317651e-05, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 957, \"end\": 966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9249808025421431, \"rank\": 0.08104253232516812, \"text\": \"Tricolour\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Other details\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 852}, {\"ngram\": \"colour degradation\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 879}, {\"ngram\": \"the T-shirt\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 894}, {\"ngram\": \"the blue sky\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 920}, {\"ngram\": \"green grass\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 936}, {\"ngram\": \"the side piping\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 985}, {\"ngram\": \"the trousers\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 1001}, {\"ngram\": \"a subtle representation\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1028}, {\"ngram\": \"the national flag\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1049}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shoes were custom made with extra layers and cushion for comfort.\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1117, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Shoes\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1057}, {\"ngram\": \"custom\", \"from\": 1063, \"to\": 1069}, {\"ngram\": \"extra layers\", \"from\": 1080, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"cushion\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1104}, {\"ngram\": \"comfort\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1116}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympic uniforms were a story I wanted to tell for Ireland.\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1175, \"end\": 1182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999637894483017, \"rank\": 3.621181260317651e-05, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympic uniforms\", \"from\": 1120, \"to\": 1140}, {\"ngram\": \"a story\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1153}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clothes change how you feel and show up and I wanted to make the best for our athletes,\\\" Weber said.\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1284, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1273, \"end\": 1278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Maria_von_Weber\", \"score\": 0.881188101580053, \"rank\": 0.13410755222664728, \"text\": \"Weber\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Maria_von_Weber\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Maria_von_Weber\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Clothes\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1191}, {\"ngram\": \"our athletes\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1270}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A textile graduate of NCAD from Rathfarnham who moved to New York in 2013, Weber is best known in Ireland for her embroidery and particularly for the coat and dress worn by US first lady Dr Jill Biden at her husband Joe Biden's inauguration as US president.\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1308, \"end\": 1312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_College_of_Art_and_Design\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NCAD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_College_of_Art_and_Design\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_College_of_Art_and_Design\"}, {\"begin\": 1318, \"end\": 1329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rathfarnham\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rathfarnham\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rathfarnham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rathfarnham\"}, {\"begin\": 1343, \"end\": 1351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999699859932, \"rank\": 3.0010159898221064e-08, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://